						<summary>

						<p>This undated record registers that, in the reign of the Noḻamba-Pallava king <hi rend="bold">Ayyapadēva, Chōrayya,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Śrīpurusayya,</hi> and the <hi rend="italic">Gāmuṇḍas</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Pannasigas</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Eraḍumura</hi> obtained the <hi rend="italic">bittuvāṭa</hi> from the king for the upkeep of the tank. <hi rend="bold">Ponnayya,</hi> the <hi rend="italic">Perggaḍe</hi> of Chōrayya wrote this and Duggāchāri engraved.</p>						

						</summary>
